The diagnostic dilemma of minimal and mild endometriosis under routine conditions. To evaluate the reliability of diagnosing minimal and mild endometriosis under routine conditions, and to determine to what extent disease activity is taken into account.Retrospective analysis (Canadian Task Force classification II-2).University teaching hospital.Laparoscopy.One hundred eighteen consecutive women with minimal and mild endometriosis undergoing routine surgery between 1994 and 1999.Analytic parameters were the total number of endometriotic lesions intraoperative description of pigmented, nonpigmented, and nondefined lesionsIntraoperative description of endometriotic lesions is inadequate. Little attention is paid to the activity of the illness. There is room for improvement in the number of excisions and histologic detection, and an attempt should be made to find a way out of this diagnostic dilemma.